MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
San Franciscan Nights -- and Days: Festival 2000, a multicultural festival of 
performing and visual arts in the parks and clubs of San Francisco, will take 
place Oct. 6-28. Over 200 performances, 1,000 artists and 50 events, including 
a "cutting edge" display of African-American, Asian, Hispanic and Native 
American talent, will be presented. The festival will open at the War Memorial 
Opera House with "Sole Night: A Celebration of Foot, Hand and Drum," with 
dancer and choreographer Katherine Dunham, the American Indian Dance Theater, 
the Mantu Theater of Chicago and the New York-based Urban Bush Women. GREG 
BRAXTON 
